(r \cos \theta)^2 +6r \sin \theta -9=0
\cos^2 \theta = 1- \sin^2 \theta
r^2 - (r \sin \theta)^2 + 6r \sin \theta -9=0
(r \sin \theta -3)^2=r^2
r=r \sin \theta -3
r= 3-r \sin \theta
r=\frac{3}{\sin \theta - 1} \lor r=\frac{3}{1+ \sin \theta} 
